          "description": "Under digital inclusiveness and inclusion, the following sub-projects are mainly included: - The \"Come on Mulan\" project combines Internet charity and insurance, and cooperates with the China Women's Development Foundation to precisely help women in need, alleviate the problems of women who have escaped poverty due to illness, return to poverty due to illness, and drop out of school due to poverty. The 23-year project continues to promote the insurance claims work in 22 counties in 22 years, and actively implements the measurement and insurance work in 23 counties in 13 provinces, cities and districts this year: \"The \"Digital Mulan Employment Training Program\" and partners such as the China Rural Development Foundation and the China Women's Development Foundation jointly use the openness, inclusiveness and flexibility of the digital age and digital employment to carry out a series of projects such as the A Bean Plan, the Rural Homestay Manager Vocational Skills Improvement Plan, the Crafts Plan, and the Township Social Worker Support Plan to help rural women's economic empowerment: \"The \"Chasing the Wind Plan\" women's football series support project allows more rural girls to enjoy the joy of sports, and inspires more women to expand more opportunities and possibilities with the spirit of women's football that dares to fight, never give up, and set no limits. The \"Chasing the Wind Project\" supports the Chinese women's football team. The Women's Football Overseas Home has been operating for 23 years and provides service guarantees for overseas women's football players. The \"Chasing the Wind Project\" supports campuses and has held two rural campus women's football leagues, with more than 60 rural primary schools participating. Football teaching skills training was provided for nearly 200 rural primary school teachers. The Rose Dream Stadium, a Chinese women's football theme stadium, was built for 6 schools, indirectly covering and driving more than 80,000 rural primary school students. The \"Family Growth Plan\u00b7Love Warms Ten Thousand Families Project\" donated to the China Women's Development Foundation, targeting the actual needs of children in difficult situations such as de facto orphaned children in 50 underdeveloped counties and their families. By establishing and empowering a grassroots care team, a service model combining normal services with professional services was established to provide precise and effective one-to-one services such as life assistance, ideological guidance, psychological care, and safety protection. - Among them, the \"Blue Vest Action\" mainly helps the elderly solve the problem of \"not daring to use or not knowing how to use\" smartphones through community lectures, public welfare exhibitions, and caravans going to the countryside. , helping to bridge the digital divide, understand anti-fraud knowledge, popularize medical and health knowledge, and let the elderly enjoy digital life. In the three years since the event was launched, it has covered 26 provincial administrative regions and 141 cities, and has cooperated with more than 100 partners to hold more than 50,000 events. 42,000 volunteers have provided offline \"face-to-face\" services to more than 1.44 million elderly people, jointly building a \"people serving people\" digital elderly service system and platform. Among them, the Blue Vest Project activities in Jingning County, Chun'an County, and Pinghu City, Zhejiang Province were supported by the \"Charity Guidance Fund of the Zhejiang Provincial Department of Civil Affairs\"; the \"Dream Chasing Action\" series of public welfare projects for the disabled were jointly initiated by the China Disabled Persons' Welfare Foundation. Through \"Come on Dream Chasers\", \"Flowers Blooming with Sound\", \"Love Without Barriers Cinema\", etc., from the start of the project to the end of 2023, 385 disabled people have been fitted with prostheses, 430 hearing and speech rehabilitation therapists have been trained, and the \"Bright Cinema\" of the China Accessible Environment Exhibition Hall has been jointly built to help the disabled with rehabilitation, education, employment, cultural life and other aspects of integrated development.",
